  "original_title": "\u2018\u201821 \u0db6\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd6 \u0d86\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dda \u0d91\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd9\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2\u2018\u2018",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"21 is not what was expected\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka Freedom Party Chairman, former President Mr. Maithripala Sirisena said today (1) that even though the government tried to clean up the 21st Amendment, it is not the kind of amendment that the people expected.",
        "The former President said that it was completely different from the 19th Amendment and that it would give the incumbent President the powers of the 20th Amendment as well as other powers until the end of his term, and hoped to make amendments to it during the Committee Stage.",
        "He also said that due to the wrong political, economic and social management of the present government, the country has gone back 70 to 80 years and is in a position to carry out home births.",
        "The former president also said that the government was not yet ready to rectify the mistakes made by appointing incompetents.",
        "Mr. Maithripala Sirisena also mentioned that all the slogans, including national security, which was the main slogan of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna during the last elections, have now been cancelled.",
        "The former President said this addressing a media briefing held at the SLFP Headquarters at Darley Road, Colombo."
      ],
